						<p>As a child I was taught "if you can't say something nice, don't say anything at all".<br />
This may have been useful in a time where people tended to be more introspective and notice (and think about) any degree of shunning.<br />
Sadly with all the push towards 'self esteem' introspection to consider what you might do better never seems to happen anymore.<br />
Instead of asking ones self what can be done better the knee jerk response is to find fault with the person offering a critisim.<br />
This is  broadly seen in politics where critisims of policy are answered with aqusations of racism.<br />
What can be expected of the average Joe when the 'leaders' on the world stage set such a fine example?</p>
